snippet: Libya’s transitional government postponed the first national election since the ouster of Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi, moving it from June 19 to July 7 to continue preparations.
abstract: Libya’s transitional government postpones the first national election since the ouster of Col Muammar el-Qaddafi until July because authorities have not yet completed the list of candidates or other arrangements for the election.

byline.contributor: Marlise Simons contributed reporting from Paris.

lead_paragraph: Libya’s transitional government postponed the first national election since the ouster of Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi, moving it from June 19 to July 7 to continue preparations.

headline.main: Libya Postpones National Election Until July, as Preparations Lag
